[2] The Philippines (Kalibo)
Date: Thu 5 Sep 2013
Source: Nation philstar.com [edited]
http://www.philstar.com/nation/2013/09/05/1175381/kalibo-under-state-calamity-over-measles-outbreak


Kalibo in Aklan province has been placed under state emergency due to an outbreak of measles in the town. Reports said members of the Sangguniang Bayan of Kalibo recently passed a resolution after a special session on Wednesday [4 Sep 2013]. The regional office of the Department of Health also recorded 15 cases of measles in the town, most of which were in Brgy. Andagao.

In the entire Western Visayas, the health department also reported 24 cases of measles.

Since January this year [2013], the Aklan Provincial Health Office registered some 77 suspected measles cases, which the Department of Health [DOH] is still evaluating. Of these suspected cases, 2 persons reportedly had died.

The DOH has observed that the month of July 2013 has seen the largest number of measles cases in the province.

[Byline: Dennis Carcamo]

